<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="140" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="11.[172,1381,1083,1905]" pageId="11" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[173,520,1713,1746]" pageId="11" pageNumber="140">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Waterhouse’s Mouse Opossum has not been assessed as a distinct species on The IUCN Red List. At the time of the last assessment, it was considered a subspecies of Linnaeus’s Mouse Opossum (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[808,1042,1792,1825]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Marmosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="11" pageNumber="140" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="murina">Marmosa murina</taxonomicName>
). Conservation status of all opossumsis being reassessed by the IUCN New World Marsupial Specialists Group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
